@Davidnet Here's a thought: demangling _ZN3Aws4Time9LocalTimeEP2tml (the symbol that's not found) results in Aws::Time::LocalTime(tm*, long).

Do you actually need aws support? Otherwise, perhaps you can retry ./configure and answer "no" to this question:
Do you wish to build TensorFlow with Amazon S3 File System support? [Y/n]:

Along the same lines, if you're not using Hadoop or Google Cloud Platform, you can say "no" for those too, to avoid unnecessary dependencies, and to get faster build times and smaller binaries.

@Davidnet Here's a thought: demangling `_ZN3Aws4Time9LocalTimeEP2tml` (the symbol that's not found) results in `Aws::Time::LocalTime(tm*, long)`.

Do you actually need aws support?  Otherwise, perhaps you can retry ./configure and answer "no" to this question:
`Do you wish to build TensorFlow with Amazon S3 File System support? [Y/n]:`

Along the same lines, if you're not using Hadoop or Google Cloud Platform, you can say "no" for those too, to avoid unnecessary dependencies, and to get faster build times and smaller binaries.
